While cruise ships have been at the center of the coronavirus storm, Callais doesn't see ships as more dangerous than other social gatherings.
"Despite the headlines, it's not as if the cruise lines are spraying passengers down with the virus," he said.
Cruise lines suspending operationsCruise lines around the globe have suspended operations for varying periods of time.
And cruise lines' suspension dates are likely to change after the extension of the CDC's "no-sail order" was announced April 9.
Some lines, including Royal Caribbean Cruise Line, Carnival Cruise Line, Princess Cruises and Holland America Line, have already issued extensions.